Heh-heh... Yer awful scrawny to be a

12:
No matter. If yer already cookin',

17: Zelimir... You're drinking at this hour?

What else have I to do?
...Less talk, more cooking, boy.
25: No. I'm about to head out, anyway.
29:

...A winery needs help with

56:
Hahaha! I wondered if this world's

70:
Yer eyes be very dark... The eyes of a

75:
More, more, more. It's never enough,
is it? Aye, you've got the eyes of a

78:
Hear me, dog. My name is Zelimir. If
yer harborin' complaints, come try

80:
As long as yer eyes be still as dark

92:
There you are, lad. Sorry to make
you bring the grub all the way out
here.
96: You helped me out earlier, after all.
98:
I also ended up with some good
alcohol to use in cooking.
102:
You're a strange boy. The tales
about yer love for cookin' don't
exaggerate.
105:
Huh... No exaggeratin', indeed. This is
much tastier than what those
Gaean lubbers had on 'em.
111:
...I've drank under the stars on me
ship countless times, but this... This is
somethin' else.
114:
Hey, lad...
What do ye say we work together?
118:
Well... I've been in this situation

You feelin' all right, boy? I ain't talkin'

132:
But yer different. Nothing's ever

145:
Besides, Alk and I already have an

I promise you'll regret it.
150:
The Crimson Blades' captain... I see.

lot.
154:
Besides, Alk's capable of so much
more than being your "right-hand
man."
157:
...Though he's much more than just
a cook, too.
161:
Tch... You've got a nasty woman on

164:
...No matter. What do you say to me

168:
I don't have any intention of joining

180: I've got one thing to say to you.
188:
A band of pirates calling themselves

191:
Seems like strange timing for you to
be asking Alk for help... Right?
Wicked Whale Zelimir?
195:
Don't tell me you're still worried

200:
Sorry, sorry! Just got a little pissed
off.
203:
He's a lot like him, you know? Using

210:
I see, I see... Those bastards are still
alive, eh?
